snippet.textDisplay: With all respect to the musicians and their efforts involved here - this sounded so artificial. If you have listened and liked NFAK singing Afreen, you understand why I am saying so. The song and the lyrics are supposed to bring out a feeling of being awe-struck by the sheer brilliance of 'thy' beauty. There is certain divinity in the way NFAK renders it - which is totally lost here. It seems like any other song, obviously sounding good due to its arrangement and inherent lyrical qualities (and people fashionably dressed!). On a lighter note, with all due respect - it seemed like RFAK was singing this with a sweet candy in mouth which he got robbed off suddenly at 5:40 when the sargam improvisation kicks off. This extra sweetness and the aggression were both uncalled for. Best of luck Coke Studio! We miss Nusrat Saab even more now!
